          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "On-call compensation and fatigue management are engineering concerns because a fatigued on-call rotation produces slower, lower-quality incident responses. The compensation framework has three components: a fixed stipend for availability, per-incident pay for off-hours interruptions, and compensatory time for high-toil shifts. Measure off-hours interruptions per engineer per shift using automated toil reports from PagerDuty data. When the toil report shows elevated or high-toil zones, run the reduction playbook in order: alert audit first, runbook automation second, business-hours reclassification third, and rotation size increase as a last resort. For GenAI services, move eval quality trend alerts and minor provider hiccup alerts out of overnight paging \u2014 they are informational, not emergencies."
          }
        ]
